    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Jackson Merrill** headlining the roster as our highest-rated option (75.10). His matchup against Sean Burke (4.35 xERA) provides an elite environment for both counting stats and stolen base potential; notably, the slow delivery from the mound boosts his efficiency score, making him a cornerstone of the lineup. **Kyle Tucker** follows closely with a 70.51 efficiency rating against the soft matchup of McGreevy. While **Kyle Tucker** faces a slight park disadvantage, the elevated SP skill profile of his opponent and his prime batting order position make him a high-floor play that should contribute heavily across our 5x5 categories.\n\nOur most critical lineup optimization decisions focused on balancing platoon advantages with sprint speed, which remains our primary focus in the scarcity-driven SB market. **Drake Baldwin** (68.14) is a locked-in start, benefiting from a favorable 4.05 xERA matchup and a projected #2 spot in the order. In the utility spot, **Marcell Ozuna** (57.48) edged out the competition, though we are monitoring weather risks throughout the day. **Coby Mayo** (53.08) was the most difficult exclusion from the starting nine; while his favorable platoon splits against Weathers were enticing, the optimizer ultimately preferred the more consistent volume and higher-leverage positioning of the current starters. \n\nRisk mitigation remains a priority as several players, including **Josh Jung**, **Josh Lowe**, **Dominic Smith**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Andy Pages**, currently feature \"Lineup Pending\" status. While we have projected their batting order based on historical data, these scores are sensitive to volatility if managers shuffle the deck late. We are particularly cautious regarding the matchup for **Josh Lowe** against Nolan McLean, as the elite 2.95 xERA presents the toughest hurdle for our lineup today. If **Josh Lowe** is dropped down the lineup card, we will be forced to reconsider his position in favor of the deeper bench options like **Nolan Schanuel** or **Miguel Vargas**.",
